---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Measure Noise"
  description="The official measurement program for the #QuietTheMowers movement. Rent a calibrated sound meter, learn the protocol, or find recommended equipment to buy."
>

<article class="section">
  <div class="container-narrow">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <p class="text-brand-600 font-semibold text-sm tracking-wider uppercase mb-4">Measure</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-display font-bold text-brand-900 leading-tight mb-6">
        Real Evidence,<br />Not Just Vibes
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-earth-500 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        The data makes the difference. We'll help you measure noise correctly, whether you rent, buy, or use your phone.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-20">
      <a href="/measure/rent" class="block bg-white border-2 border-brand-200 rounded-2xl p-8 text-center hover:border-brand-400 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-brand-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-5">
          <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-brand-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-display font-bold text-brand-900 mb-2">Rent a Meter</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-earth-500">
          Borrow a calibrated Class 2 sound meter. You pay shipping. We ship anywhere in the US.
        </p>
        <span class="inline-block mt-4 text-brand-600 font-semibold text-sm">$15&ndash;25 shipping &rarr;</span>
      </a>

      <a href="/measure/buy" class="block bg-white border border-earth-200 rounded-2xl p-8 text-center hover:border-brand-300 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-accent-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-5">
          <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-accent-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 3h2l.4 2M7 13h10l4-8H5.4M7 13L5.4 5M7 13l-2.293 2.293c-.63.63-.184 1.707.707 1.707H17m0 0a2 2 0 100 4 2 2 0 000-4zm-8 2a2 2 0 100 4 2 2 0 000-4z"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-display font-bold text-brand-900 mb-2">Buy Equipment</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-earth-500">
          Curated recommendations with Amazon links. Budget meters, professional gear, and smartphone alternatives.
        </p>
        <span class="inline-block mt-4 text-accent-600 font-semibold text-sm">View recommendations &rarr;</span>
      </a>

      <a href="/measure/protocol" class="block bg-white border border-earth-200 rounded-2xl p-8 text-center hover:border-brand-300 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-earth-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-5">
          <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-earth-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12h6m-6 4h6m2 5H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-display font-bold text-brand-900 mb-2">The Protocol</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-earth-500">
          Official measurement protocol: distance, height, duration, time of day. Printable PDF included.
        </p>
        <span class="inline-block mt-4 text-earth-600 font-semibold text-sm">Read the protocol &rarr;</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="prose mx-auto">
      <h2>Why Measurement Matters</h2>

      <p>Policy change runs on evidence. When you walk into a city council meeting or HOA board session armed with real noise data, the conversation changes. Instead of debating whether there's a problem, you're discussing which solution to adopt.</p>

      <p>Our measurement program makes this easy:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Rent</strong> a calibrated Class 2 meter for 7&ndash;14 days (you pay shipping only, typically $15&ndash;25 round-trip)</li>
        <li><strong>Buy</strong> your own meter using our curated recommendations (we earn a small affiliate commission that funds the platform)</li>
        <li><strong>Use your phone</strong> with our recommended apps and calibration protocol</li>
        <li><strong>Upload</strong> your data and attach it to a campaign or save it as a personal record</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How the Data Gets Used</h2>

      <p>Measurements you upload can be:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>Attached to a specific campaign to support a petition</li>
        <li>Aggregated into regional noise heatmaps (anonymized or public, your choice)</li>
        <li>Used to generate speaker cards and handouts for council meetings</li>
        <li>Cited in press coverage and social media campaigns</li>
      </ul>

      <p>Your privacy matters. Every measurement has three visibility options: public, anonymous-public ("a user in 80303"), or private. You control how your data appears.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 bg-brand-50 rounded-2xl p-10 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-brand-900 mb-4">Ready to Start Measuring?</h2>
      <p class="text-earth-600 mb-8 max-w-lg mx-auto">
        Rent a meter, buy your own, or learn the protocol. Good data wins arguments.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/measure/rent" class="btn-primary text-lg px-8 py-4">
          Rent a Meter
        </a>
        <a href="/measure/protocol" class="btn-secondary text-lg px-8 py-4">
          Read the Protocol
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>

</Layout>
